{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vimeo/psalm/issues/5049","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vimeo/psalm","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vimeo/psalm/issues/5049/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vimeo/psalm/issues/5049/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vimeo/psalm/issues/5049/events","html_url":"https://github.com/vimeo/psalm/issues/5049","id":789004588,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWU3ODkwMDQ1ODg=","number":5049,"title":"Regression: `@psalm-assert !empty` with `bool` does not reduce it to `true`","user":{"login":"Ocramius","id":154256,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE1NDI1Ng==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/154256?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Ocramius","html_url":"https://github.com/Ocramius","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Ocramius/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Ocramius/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Ocramius/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Ocramius/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Ocramius/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Ocramius/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Ocramius/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Ocramius/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Ocramius/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2021-01-19T13:02:53Z","updated_at":"2021-01-19T22:19:53Z","closed_at":"2021-01-19T22:19:53Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"While writing type refinements for `webmozart/assert`, I found a regression between `vimeo/psalm@61f5a06` (61f5a06) and `vimeo/psalm:4.4.1` (9fd7a7).\r\n\r\nhttps://psalm.dev/r/6d6857dcf8\r\n\r\nSpecifically:\r\n\r\n```php\r\n/** @psalm-assert !empty $input */\r\nfunction assertNotEmpty(mixed $input): void { /* ... */ }\r\n\r\n/** @psalm-return true */\r\nfunction gimmeTrue(bool $input): bool {\r\n    assertNotEmpty($input);\r\n    \r\n    return $input;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nProduces:\r\n\r\n```\r\nPsalm output (using commit 2f58c6a): \r\n\r\nERROR: InvalidReturnStatement - 10:12 - The inferred type 'bool' does not match the declared return type 'true' for gimmeTrue\r\n\r\nERROR: InvalidReturnType - 6:19 - The declared return type 'true' for gimmeTrue is incorrect, got 'bool'\r\n \r\nPsalm detected 1 fixable issue(s)\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen given a `bool` `$input`, I would expect this to infer `true` as result of the assertion: this used to work in `3.x` (61f5a06).\r\n\r\nThe opposite works:\r\n\r\n```php\r\n/** @psalm-assert empty $input */\r\nfunction assertEmpty(mixed $input): void { /* ... */ }\r\n\r\n/** @psalm-return false */\r\nfunction gimmeTrue(bool $input): bool {\r\n    assertEmpty($input);\r\n    \r\n    return $input;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nhttps://psalm.dev/r/ff0756f05d","closed_by":{"login":"muglug","id":2292638,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIyOTI2Mzg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2292638?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug","html_url":"https://github.com/muglug","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/repos","events_url":"https://api